{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionIn recent years, artificial intelligence (AI) has become one of the most discussed and rapidly advancing fields in the world of technology.",
    "The development of theories, methods, algorithms, and applications to simulate and augment human intelligence has been the focus of AI's progression [1].",
    "A specialized form of AI, known as Large Language Models (LLMs), is used in natural language processing (NLP).",
    "These models, trained on vast amounts of textual data, can perform tasks such as generating human-like text, understanding language, translating, and summarizing [2].",
    "Among the most widely used AI chatbots today are LLMs like Chat Generative Pre-Trained Transformer (ChatGPT), developed by OpenAI in November 2022, and Gemini, developed by Google DeepMind for being launched in 2023 [3]."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The development of theories, methods, algorithms, and applications to simulate and augment human intelligence has been the focus of AI's progression [1].",
